This same theme applies to practically all of our thinking errors: self-knowledge is surprisingly useless. Teaching people about the hazards of multitasking doesnt lead to less texting in the car; learning about the weakness of the will doesnt increase the success of diets; knowing that most people are overconfident about the future doesnt make us more realistic. The problem isnt that were stupidits that were so damn stubborn.


